lish-speaking world."],"variants":[{"name":"Isabel","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Isabelle de Roquefeull was born in 1210, in France, her father, Raymond de Roquefeull, was 33 and her mother, Delphine or Dauphine de Turenne, was 30. She married Comte Hughes de Rodez in 1230, in France. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1210–":"1210–Surnud","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1200–1274":"1200–1274","1236–1303":"1236–1303","1177–Male":"1177–Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","environ 1236":"umbes 1236","1303":"1303","1203":"1203","1236":"1236","1200":"1200","1210":"1210","1177":"1177","1230":"1230","1274":"1274","1180":"1180","Turenne-Gare, Corrèze, Limousin, France":"Turenne-Gare, Corrèze, Limousin, Prantsusmaa","Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France":"Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, Prantsusmaa","Roquefeull, France":"Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1210–":"1210–Kuollut","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1200–1274":"1200–1274","1236–1303":"1236–1303","1177–Male":"1177–Kuollut","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","environ 1236":"noin 1236","1303":"1303","1203":"1203","1236":"1236","1200":"1200","1210":"1210","1177":"1177","1230":"1230","1274":"1274","1180":"1180","Turenne-Gare, Corrèze, Limousin, France":"Turenne-Gare, Corrèze, Limousin, Ranska","R